Today I developed my understanding of how variables work in JavaScript. It is similar to Python and C#.
I learnt about Statements, Comments, different variable keywords such as const, let and var. I also learnt the "typeof" keyword in JavaScript which outputs the date type.
I then finally learnt how to take in input with the "prompt()" keyword.
So to put my newly learnt JavaScript skills to the test, I made a simple Arithmatic calculator which takes in two numbers and does either + - / or *.


Here is the Code:
<script>
const num1 = prompt("Enter number 1: ");
let num1_up = Number(num1);

const num2 = prompt("Enter number 2: ");
let num2_up = Number(num2);

const op = prompt("Pick one operator: + - / * ");

if (op == "+") {
	add_ans = num1_up + num2_up;
	alert(add_ans)
    }
else if (op == "-") {
	minus_ans = num1_up - num2_up;
	alert(minus_ans)
    }


else if (op == "/") {
	div_ans = num1_up / num2_up;
	alert(div_ans)
    }


else if (op == "*") {
	multiply_ans = num1_up * num2_up;
	alert(multiply_ans)
    }


</script>
